cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Brain Researcher in academic work, please cite both the software and the accompanying paper (when available)."
title: "Brain Researcher: An LLM-driven Research Assistant for Neuroimaging"
abstract: >-
  Brain Researcher combines large-language-model planning with a
  neuroscience knowledge graph (Neo4j), a curated catalog of
  fMRI/diffusion/EEG analysis tools, and an evidence-grounded
  scientific-review system. It converts natural-language research
  questions into reproducible analyses, with every step traceable to
  its plan, inputs, and primary literature.
type: software
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/zjc062/brain_researcher"
url: "https://github.com/zjc062/brain_researcher"
# Update at v1.0 release:
# - `version`, `date-released`, `doi` (Zenodo) below
# - the `preferred-citation` block (arXiv preprint)
version: "0.0-dev"
authors:
